news.title: Uttar Pradesh governor distributes certificates, house keys to beneficiaries in Mirzapur
news.para: ​​The Governor praised the work of the Green Army in addressing social issues and stressed the importance of education for both boys and girls.

news.title: Amaravati capital progress drives real estate boom near Vijayawada West Bypass
news.para: The sector had faced stagnation during the previous government's tenure, as speculations about relocating the capital to Visakhapatnam discouraged investors.

news.title: Property registration locations in Indore merged for new guideline rates
news.para: The process has been undertaken through polygon mapping reducing the total number of registration locations from 5,124 to 4,613 in the city.

news.title: No flat 10% rise in RR rates across state: Maharashtra revenue minister
news.para: "There are news reports that the RR rate will be increased by 10-15%, but this is false. RR rates were last increased in 2022-23. A survey was carried out across the state, and I strictly warned there cannot be any arbitrary hike," he said.

news.title: Chandigarh: CHB's sector 53 housing scheme’s future under cloud again
news.para: In the recently concluded demand survey for the scheme, nearly 7,500 applicants expressed their interest. In a previous survey (2018-19), the scheme received only 178 applications.

news.title: Mumbai: FIR against Wadhwa Group for cheating Policon Realtors of Rs 57 crore
news.para: ​The FIR alleged that Wadhwa Group directors, including Navin Makhija, failed to honour financial commitments made in the agreement despite receiving additional floor space index (FSI) and funds as part of a settlement deal.

news.title: Flats in Greater Noida to get costlier as land prices likely to go up
news.para: The proposed hike, expected to be approved in the March board meeting, will affect all land categories including residential, commercial, industrial, and institutional plots.

news.title: New Prayagraj master plan to add 639 villages to city’s municipal limits
news.para: In this, a plan was made to convert many residential areas, including Civil Lines, into commercial buildings. After this, objections were sought from the people. About 485 people gave objections and suggestions.

news.title: Pending MahaRERA recovery cases to be disposed of within three months: Maharashtra minister
news.para: The latest data from MahaRERA reveals that only 316 recovery warrant complaints out of a total of 1,342 in the state have been executed by the collectorates.

news.title: Telangana RERA fines construction firm for deviating from plan
news.para: ​The penalty followed complaints from the apartment flat owners co-op maintenance society, which alleged that the developer deviated from the approved project plan and denied society members access to promised amenities.

news.title: Bhopal collector appears in Madhya Pradesh HC in contempt petition
news.para: Referring to the non-execution of the RRC order of the Real Estate Regulatory Authority (RERA) despite the direction of the high court, Singh told the court that Deputy Secretary, RERA, H P Verma informed him about a stay on the RERA order granted by the Supreme Court.

news.title: Soaring construction material costs in Tamil Nadu threaten stability
news.para: The Southern Lorry Owners Welfare Association has made an appeal to chief minister M K Stalin, emphasising the crippling impact on both public and private construction projects.

news.title: Consortium of lenders of Jaiprakash Associates transfers debt to NARCL
news.para: ​Jaiprakash Associates Ltd (JAL) in a regulatory filing informed that the consortium of lenders of the company have "assigned/transferred their outstanding debt/financial assets along with underlying securities interest, pledge of shares, guarantees, receivables etc. charged for financial assistance granted by them to JAL in favour of NARCL".

news.title: Notices served on 1.5 lakh PMAY-G beneficiaries for not constructing pucca houses: Bihar minister
news.para: ​Rural Development Minister Sharwan Kumar, speaking in the assembly on Wednesday, said the department has also lodged certificate cases against 19,495 defaulters for not building their houses under the scheme despite the government sanctioning the total amount (all instalments) several months ago.

news.title: Individual housing loans in Delhi surge 14% to Rs 33.53 lakh crore in 2024: NHB report
news.para: Individual housing loan disbursements were recorded at Rs 4.10 lakh crore during the half-year that ended September 2024, while for the full financial year 2023-24, disbursements reached Rs 9.07 lakh crore.

news.title: Mizoram assembly adopts central land acquisition law for fair compensation
news.para: "The Right to Fair Compensation and Transparency in Land Acquisition, Rehabilitation and Resettlement Act, 2013," already applicable across India, was officially adopted in Mizoram following the passage of the resolution in the Assembly.

news.title: Tenders worth Rs 37,702 crore approved for Amaravati development: Andhra Pradesh Minister
news.para: ​​These projects will commence immediately after the Cabinet's approval on March 17, he said in an official statement on Tuesday.

news.title: Ludhiana civic body demolishes six more illegal buildings
news.para: The officials said three illegal industrial buildings under construction were demolished in Kundanpuri, while a labour quarters under construction was razed in Pritam Nagar.

news.title: Kerala HC imposes construction ban at Parunthumpara
news.para: The SIT, headed by IG K Sethuraman, reported extensive encroachments on govt land. On Monday, a special revenue team demolished a large crucifix erected on encroached land at Parunthumpara.

news.title: Nashik civic body rakes in 50% of total property tax via online mode
news.para: Before the Covid-19 pandemic, NMC's online property tax payment was only 7%. This shift towards digital payments indicated a growing trend towards online convenience.
